New Records: De'Aaron Fox scored a game-high 29 points and 10 assists for the Sacramento Kings.
Domantas Sabonis recorded a double-double with 11 points and 10 rebounds.
Sacramento Kings won their second consecutive game against the Phoenix Suns.
Key Match Events: The Kings' decisive 29-14 run in the final nine minutes, including multiple three-pointers by Kevin Huerter and Keon Ellis, which shifted momentum.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sacramento Kings outshot Phoenix Suns 64.1% to 37.1%
Phoenix Suns were playing their second game in two nights.
Trey Lyles and Jordan McLaughlin contributed with double figures for the Kings.
